All black pieces are now well placed - even the rook on h8 is joining the action. The threat is ...Ng4. White would then have to play g2-g3 to prevent checkmate on h2. This later allows Black to play the pawn break ...h5-h4, opening up the h-file. White lacks defenders on the kingside.} 11. Na4 $2 {The hope that the bishop will leave its strong diagonal is headed for disappointment.} Bd4 12. c3 Ng4 {A strong intermezzo that prepares the following sequence.} 13. g3 Bxf2+ $1 14. Rxf2 Nxf2 15. Kxf2 h4 {The h-file opens and the white king comes under attack. The knight on a4 is also very vulnerable. Black is clearly better. A recent example is the game Akdag-Camlar [/variation/31423333/#/15/b], Konya 2022 (0-1).} *

