r pieces and is slightly better. The focus of Black's play will be on the queenside, where the knight on c3 provides a favorable target for attack. Typical ideas include ...Bb4xc3 or ...a7-a6 and b7-b5 followed by the knight maneuver ...Ne5-c4.} *

