ccessible to the white pieces, and Bc4 with an attack on f7 is also an option.}) 8. e5 {Nd6} {This intermediate move is more accurate than the immediate 8...Ne8. Primarily, Black wants to drive away the b5 knight in order to have the option of ...Bc5-d4 later. Ne8 Ne4 is slightly better for White, because Black does not have the active reaction ...Bc5-d4 here. After exf6 Qxf6! , Black wins back the piece under favorable circumstances.} Ne8 {Nde4?} 9. Qh5 {Now there are many good moves for Black.} f6 $1 {This refutes White's setup. White is losing a pawn, either on e5 or f2.} 10. exf6 Nxf6 ({Very strong is also} 10... d5 {.}) *

