hite lacks the resource 11.Nb5 at this point. On 10...Bxh2? , 11.Kh1 follows, and due to the threats of 12.g3 or 12.f4, Black can't recapture on d5.}) ({➤ After} 8... Bc5 {, the pin} 9. Bg5 {can become annoying.}) 9. Re1 O-O 10. e5 {It's up to White to demonstrate that the position is still equal. The bishop on d3 can be exchanged with ...Nc5 or ...a7-a5 followed by ...Ba6. The black rook can operate on the semi-open b-file. Qg4?! The most common move in practice. White plays for a kingside attack. f5! An important resource. If White captures on f6, the black minor pieces become very active. If White retreats the queen, the white minor pieces are left looking at Black's solid pawn chain and the pawn on e5 becomes weak. Black is better.} *

