ing theory.} Qc7 ({The main move. Black attacks the e5-pawn and forces a weakening of White's position. The alternative} 8... Bb7 {is also popular nowadays. Black wants to play ...c6-c5 and quickly solve the problem of the 'bad' light-squared bishop.}) 9. f4 {The queen has fulfilled its purpose on c7 and moves to a better square. On b6, the queen performs a number of functions:  * It controls the weakened a7-g1 diagonal.  * It threatens the double attack 10...Qb4+.  * It attacks the b2-pawn, complicating the development of the c1-bishop.  * It supports ...Ne3.  * It supports the attempt to exchange the light-squared bishops with ...Ba6. Bd3 The second most common move after 10.c4. White develops the bishop and defends against Black's threats.} Ba6 {The downside of White's last move. Black can now force the exchange of bishops.} 10. a3 ({A natural developing move, but there are also other good moves available, for example} 10. f5 {or}) (10. Qd4 {.}) ({c4} 10. Qe2 {and}) (10. Bxa6 {have also been played. In those lines, Black achieves a comfortable position after natural moves. After}) (10. c4 {on the other hand, a precise response is required.}) {Qd4! of c4. The current version is comparatively better for White, as Black does not have the resource} 10... Nb4 {Nonetheless, Black doesn't have any problems.} 11. Qe2 Rb8 {Moves with the f-pawn are also good. 13...Rb8 is threatening ...Rb3. White has only one defense. Rf1} 12. f5 {A familiar idea. Here, White must exchange on f6. exf6} (12. Ng3 $2 {Bd8-+ and ...Ba5+ is a deadly threat.}) {gxf6 Black has the initiative. There is a threat of ...f6-f5 and ...Rb3. With the precise 16.Rf3 White maintains the balance. Rf3! Now the d3-bishop is defended, and thus the knight on d5 is under attack. Rb3!? This leads to a sacrifice of the exchange. Qg1+ is also a good move. Nf2 Nb6 Qd1 This is threatening both Qxb3 and Bg6+ followed by Qxd4, so Black's response is forced. Rxd3 Qxd3 Qxd3 Rxd3} 12... Bc4 {For the exchange, Black has a pawn, the bishop pair, and a mobile pawn mass in the center. Black is at least not worse.} *

