omething to show for the pawn. Ba6} 10. Qe3 $1 Z0 ({With precise moves, White manages to equalize. There might follow: Rfe1} 10... O-O {cxd5 exd5} 11. Ba6 {Qxa6 Qd3 Qc6 c4 , and White regains the pawn.}) *

