 for Black. 13...Qe7 would not have worked one move earlier because White could have taken on d4.}) ({Ke7! This looks risky, but White has no dangerous discovered check. In fact, 14...Ke7 is the only good move. After other king moves, White could take on d4, but now the knight is attacked. Nxc8+ Kf6 Knight and queen of White are attacked, therefore Black wins back the piece. Precision is still needed. Qd2 Nxd3+ Necessary. There was a threat of 17.Qf4+, winning a piece. cxd3 Qc7! Another accurate move. The knight on c8 is trapped and can still be captured a move later. First, Black prevents the check on f4. Next, Black wants to bring the rook on h8 into play and then go back to f8 with the king, where it is safe. White does not have sufficient compensation for the pawn. Rxc8 Qf4+} 10... Ke7 {Qg5+ Kf8 Qc5+ Kg8 . The active placement of the queen gives White good compensation.}) *

