17... Ne4 $1 ({Much stronger than} 17... Ne8 $2 {, which was played in the game but allowed} 18. Nd4 $14 {with the blockade of the d-pawn.}) 18. Nxe4 ({After} 18. Nxd5 Bxd5 19. Rxd5 Rce8 $1 {the white knight has no good retreat square: A)} 20. Nd6 Nxd6 21. Qxd6 Rxe2 {. B) 20.Nc7 Re7-+ . C) 20.Na3 Nb4-+ .}) 18... dxe4 {As a result of the exchange, the black bishop has become active and targets the white king's position.} 19. Nd6 {The point. Black doesn't need to worry about the material but can focus on the attack. If instead 19.Nc3 , 19...Nb4! would give black a strong attack as well. Nxc8 Rxc8-+ The threats of ...Rxc2+ and ...Nxa2+ give Black a decisive attack.} *

