{In the pawn sacrifice variation 6.Be2, positions with opposite-colored bishops often arise. In these positions, king safety is particularly important.} 16. Qg5 $1 ({The mating threat on e7 forces a weakening of the black king's position. Much weaker is} 16. Qxg7 $2 O-O-O {and the black king is safe.}) 16... f6 17. Qxg7 {Once again, there is a mating threat on e7.} O-O-O 18. Bd6 $1 {That's why the pawn had to be lured to f6. Black has no satisfactory defense against the mating threat on c7.} Rxd6 ({➤} 18... Bd7 19. Rac1 {wins the queen.}) ({➤ The move played in the game,} 18... Ba4 {, did not help either. The fastest way to win now would have been} 19. Rab1 {.}) 19. Qxh8+ *

